3174	    lem:overEquivalence_inverse_isContinuous, lem:opens_overEquivalence_mathlib,
3175	    lem:pushforwardPushforwardEquivalence_mathlib, lem:modules_restrictFunctor_mathlib,
3176	    lem:modules_restrictFunctorIsoPullback_mathlib, lem:isLocalization_basicOpen_mathlib}
3177	  The isomorphism is built in four steps, ascending from the purely topological layer to the
3178	  module-level statement.
3179	
3180	  \emph{Step 1 (topological layer --- done).} The opens functor of the open immersion
3181	  \(U.\iota\) realizes the slice of the opens site of \(X\) over \(U\) as the opens site of the
3182	  subspace \(U\); on sheaf categories this is the equivalence
3183	  \(\mathrm{Sheaf}(J_X|_U,\,A) \simeq \mathrm{Sheaf}(J_U,\,A)\) of
3184	  \cref{def:overEquivalence_sheafCongr}, for every target category \(A\). This is the
3185	  topos-theoretic layer, assembled from the cocontinuity/continuity of both legs of
3186	  \(\mathrm{Opens.overEquivalence}\,U\) (\cref{lem:opens_overEquivalence_mathlib}).
3187	
