3189	  sliced structure sheaf \(\mathcal{O}_X.\mathrm{over}\,U\) with the structure sheaf
3190	  \(\mathcal{O}_{U}\) of the open subscheme \(U.\mathrm{toScheme}\), transported across the
3191	  \(\mathrm{RingCat}\)-valued instance of \cref{def:overEquivalence_sheafCongr}; this is an
3192	  isomorphism of sheaves of rings. The bridge is the factorization of the opens functor of the
3193	  immersion,
3194	  \[
3195	    U.\iota.\mathrm{opensFunctor}
3196	      \;=\; (\mathrm{Opens.overEquivalence}\,U).\mathrm{inverse}
3197	        \;\circ\; \mathrm{Over.forget}\,U ,
3198	  \]
3199	  under which the structure-sheaf comparison reduces to the standard open-immersion
3200	  structure-sheaf identifications; recall that \(\mathrm{restrictFunctor}\,U.\iota\)
3201	  (\cref{lem:modules_restrictFunctor_mathlib}) is precisely pushforward along
3202	  \(U.\iota.\mathrm{opensFunctor}\). This ring-sheaf identification is the remaining geometric
3203	  obstacle.
3204	
3205	  \emph{Step 3 (lift to modules).} Given the step-2 identification of the underlying ring sheaves
3206	  and the continuity of both legs (\cref{lem:overEquivalence_functor_isContinuous},
3207	  \cref{lem:overEquivalence_inverse_isContinuous}), lift the sheaf-of-rings comparison to an
3208	  equivalence of categories of sheaves of modules via
3209	  \(\mathrm{pushforwardPushforwardEquivalence}\)
3210	  (\cref{lem:pushforwardPushforwardEquivalence_mathlib}). Under this equivalence the sliced
3211	  module \(M.\mathrm{over}\,U\) corresponds to the geometric restriction
3212	  \((\mathrm{restrictFunctor}\,U.\iota).\mathrm{obj}\,M\).
3213	
3214	  \emph{Step 4 (compose).} Compose with
3215	  \(\mathrm{restrictFunctorIsoPullback}\) (\cref{lem:modules_restrictFunctorIsoPullback_mathlib})
3216	  to land the isomorphism \(M.\mathrm{over}\,U \cong M.\mathrm{restrict}\,U.\iota \cong
3217	  U.\iota^{*}M\). The two sides live a priori in different module categories, so the literal Lean
3218	  statement of \(\mathrm{overRestrictIso}\) is phrased through the step-3 equivalence functor; for
3219	  \(X = \Spec R\) and \(U = D(r)\) the target is \((\Spec R_r).\mathrm{Modules}\) under
3220	  \(D(r) \cong \Spec R_r\) (\cref{lem:isLocalization_basicOpen_mathlib}).
3221	\end{proof}
