4941	  Two pairs \((\mathcal{F}, q)\) and \((\mathcal{F}', q')\) are equivalent iff
4942	  \(\ker(q) = \ker(q')\). On morphisms \(f : T' \to T\) over \(S\), the functor
4943	  acts by pulling back the quotient along \(X_{T'} \to X_T\) (well-defined
4944	  since tensor product is right-exact and preserves both flatness and
4945	  properness). The Hilbert scheme is the special case
4946	  \(\Hilb^{\Phi,L}_{X/S} := \Quot^{\Phi,L}_{\mathcal{O}_X/X/S}\).
4947	\end{definition}
