5093	% SOURCE QUOTE PROOF: see the "Construction of Grassmannian" sub-section of
5094	% [Nitsure], \S 1 (references/nitsure-hilbert-quot-src/nitsure-hilbert-quot.tex,
5095	% L773-L930), which gives the construction in five named steps
5096	% ("Construction by gluing together affine patches", "Separatedness",
5097	% "Properness", "Universal quotient", "Projective embedding"). The total
5098	% verbatim text is ~150 lines; it is reproduced piecewise in the
5099	% SOURCE QUOTE comment of the theorem statement above.
5100	\begin{proof}
5101	  
5102	  Over \(S = \Spec \mathbb{Z}\) and \(V = \mathcal{O}_S^{\oplus r}\) the
5103	  Grassmannian \(\mathrm{Gr}(r, d)\) is constructed by gluing
5104	  \(\binom{r}{d}\) affine charts \(U^I = \Spec\mathbb{Z}[X^I]\) indexed by
5105	  size-\(d\) subsets \(I \subseteq \{1, \dots, r\}\). The chart \(U^I\)
5106	  carries the matrix \(X^I\) of size \(d \times r\) whose \(I\)-th \(d \times d\)
5107	  minor is the identity, with the remaining \(d(r-d)\) entries free
5108	  variables (so \(U^I \cong \mathbb{A}^{d(r-d)}_{\mathbb{Z}}\)). The
5109	  transition maps \(\theta_{I,J} : U^I \cap U^J \to U^J \cap U^I\) defined
5110	  by \(X^J \mapsto (X^I_J)^{-1} X^I\) on the locus where \(\det X^I_J\) is
5111	  invertible satisfy the cocycle condition
5112	  \(\theta_{I,K} = \theta_{I,J} \circ \theta_{J,K}\). The glued
5113	  \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d) \to \Spec\mathbb{Z}\) is smooth of relative dimension
5114	  \(d(r-d)\). Separatedness is checked from the diagonal
5115	  \(\Delta_{I,J} \subset U^I \times U^J\) cut out by \(X^J_I X^I - X^J = 0\).
5116	  Properness follows from the valuative criterion for DVRs: given
5117	  \(\varphi : \Spec K \to \mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) over a DVR \(R\) with fraction
5118	  field \(K\), factoring through some chart \(U^I\) via a ring map
5119	  \(f : \mathbb{Z}[X^I] \to K\), choose \(J\) minimising the valuation
5120	  \(\nu(f(P^I_J))\) of the minor; on the chart \(U^J\) all entries have
5121	  non-negative valuation, so \(f\) extends uniquely to \(\Spec R\).
5122	
5123	  The universal quotient \(u : \mathcal{O}_{\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)}^{\oplus r}
5124	  \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal{U}\) is given on \(U^I\) by the matrix \(X^I\)
5125	  and glued by \(g_{I,J} = (X^I_J)^{-1} \in GL_d(U^I \cap U^J)\). The
5126	  determinant line bundle \(\det\mathcal{U}\) has transition functions
5127	  \(\det g_{I,J} = 1/P^I_J\); the global sections
5128	  \(\sigma_I \in \Gamma(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d), \det\mathcal{U})\) defined by
5129	  \(\sigma_I|_{U^J} = P^J_I\) form a base-point-free linear system separating
5130	  points over \(\Spec\mathbb{Z}\), giving an embedding into
5131	  \(\mathbb{P}^{\binom{r}{d}-1}_{\mathbb{Z}}\), which is closed by
5132	  properness. Representability of \(\mathrm{Grass}(r,d)\) is then verified
5133	  on the universal pair \((\mathrm{Gr}(r,d), u)\): a quotient
5134	  \(q : \mathcal{O}_T^{\oplus r} \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal{F}\) of
5135	  rank \(d\) on \(T\) is everywhere locally trivialised; on the locus where
5136	  the columns indexed by \(I\) are a basis the matrix of \(q\) has the form
5137	  \(X^I\), defining the classifying morphism \(T \to U^I \subset
5138	  \mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\). Base change from \(\mathbb{Z}\) to a general noetherian
5139	  base \(S\) with a vector bundle \(V\) is direct: trivialise \(V\) on an open
5140	  cover and glue. For non-trivial \(V\) the same construction produces
5141	  \(\mathrm{Gr}_S(V, d)\) with Pl\"ucker embedding into
5142	  \(\mathbb{P}_S(\bigwedge^d V)\).
5143	\end{proof}
