5148	This chapter packages \emph{only} the Quot-foundations layer: the Hilbert
5149	polynomial, the Quot functor, and the Grassmannian scheme with its
5150	representability. The following are explicitly out of scope here:
5151	\begin{itemize}
5152	  \item \textbf{Representability of the Quot scheme} -- the
5153	    Grothendieck--Altman--Kleiman existence theorem and its proof skeleton
5154	    (boundedness, Grassmannian embedding, flattening stratification,
5155	    valuative criterion) are not constructed in this chapter.
5156	  \item \textbf{Flat base change of cohomology} (Stacks 02KH) and its
5157	    associated prerequisites -- not constructed in this chapter.
5158	  \item \textbf{Hilbert scheme as a separate chapter}. The Hilbert scheme
5159	    \(\Hilb_{X/S}\) is the special case
5160	    \(\Hilb_{X/S} = \Quot_{\mathcal{O}_X/X/S}\) of the Quot functor and is
5161	    introduced inline (\cref{def:quot_functor}); no separate chapter.
5162	  \item \textbf{Snapper's Lemma} -- the polynomial-eventually property of
5163	    Euler characteristics, used in \cref{def:hilbert_polynomial}. Cited
5164	    via Nitsure \S 1 and (textbook reference) Hartshorne III.5.2;
5165	    Lean formalization is a prerequisite sub-task.
